.\" Manual page for the ves command line interface to libVES.
.\" Keep in sync with the VEShelp string in src/ves-util/help.c and with the
.\" option parser in src/ves-util.c.  Version: VESUTIL_VERSION_CODE.
.TH VES 1 "2026-06-17" "ves 1.08" "VES Manual"
.SH NAME
ves \- command line interface to libVES (VESvault encrypt\-everything API)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ves
.RI [ authentication ]
.IR operation " [" operation " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ves
is the command line interface to
.BR libVES ,
the VESvault API library for end\-to\-end encryption.  It performs key
management and exchange, Vault Item encryption and sharing, and stream
encryption against a VES repository.
.PP
A typical invocation first authenticates and selects a Vault \(em
.B \-A
for a VES account / Primary Vault, or
.B \-a
for an App Vault \(em optionally unlocking it with a local Encryption Key
Store
.RB ( \-E )
or a VESkey
.RB ( \-u ),
then performs one or more operations on Vault Items
.RB ( \-o ),
Vault Keys
.RB ( \-k ),
or stream ciphers.
.PP
Most options that set a value have a corresponding
.B \-p
form that prints the current value instead (for example
.B \-ip
prints a Vault Item's content), and an
.BI \- X pf
.I FILE
form that reads the value from, or writes it to, a file.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Authentication and Vault Management
.TP
\fB\-a\fP \fIURI\fP, \fB\-\-account=\fP\fIURI\fP
Select an App Vault.
.br
\fIURI\fP = "[ves:]//domain/externalId/"
.TP
\fB\-A\fP \fIEMAIL\fP, \fB\-\-primary\-account=\fP\fIEMAIL\fP
Select a VES Account / Primary Vault.
.br
\fIEMAIL\fP = "email" | "ves:////email"
.TP
\fB\-E\fP [\fIflag\fP[,\fIflag\fP...]], \fB\-\-keystore\fP[=\fIflag\fP,...]
Use a local Encryption Key Store.  Use
.B \-El
to list the available Key Store flags.
.TP
\fB\-u\fP \fIVESKEY\fP, \fB\-\-unlock=\fP\fIVESKEY\fP
Unlock the App Vault using \fIVESKEY\fP.  \fB\-uf\fP \fIFILE\fP reads the
VESkey from \fIFILE\fP; \fB\-up\fP, \fB\-upf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the App
Vault VESkey (\fB\-A\fP required).
.TP
\fB\-T\fP \fITOKEN\fP, \fB\-\-token=\fP\fITOKEN\fP
Apply a Session Token.  \fB\-Tp\fP, \fB\-Tpf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the current
Session Token.
.TP
\fB\-L\fP, \fB\-\-lock\fP
Keep the Vault locked.
.TP
\fB\-n\fP, \fB\-\-new\fP
Create a new App Vault (\fB\-a\fP & \fB\-A\fP required; \fB\-G\fP | \fB\-y\fP
| \fB\-u\fP are used if provided).
.SS Vault Item Operations
.TP
\fB\-o\fP \fIURI\fP, \fB\-\-vault\-item=\fP\fIURI\fP
Select a Vault Item.
.br
\fIURI\fP = "[ves:][//domain/]externalId"
.TP
\fB\-i\fP \fIDATA\fP, \fB\-\-item=\fP\fIDATA\fP
Set the raw content of the Vault Item.  \fB\-if\fP \fIFILE\fP takes the
content from \fIFILE\fP (size limits apply; use \fB\-P\fP & \fB\-C\fP for
large files); \fB\-ip\fP, \fB\-ipf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the raw content.
.TP
\fB\-s\fP \fIURI\fP[,\fIURI\fP...], \fB\-\-share=\fP\fIURI\fP[,...]
Share the Vault Item with the specified Vaults; any existing shares remain
intact.
.br
\fIURI\fP = "[ves:][//domain/]externalId/[userRef]"
.TP
\fB\-r\fP \fIURI\fP[,\fIURI\fP...], \fB\-\-unshare=\fP\fIURI\fP[,...]
Stop sharing the Vault Item with the specified Vaults.
.TP
\fB\-S\fP \fIURI\fP[,\fIURI\fP...], \fB\-\-set\-share=\fP\fIURI\fP[,...]
Share the Vault Item with the specified Vaults; any other shares are
removed.  \fB\-Sp\fP, \fB\-Spf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the share list, one
entry per line:
.br
key_id <SP> key_uri <SP> key_type
.TP
\fB\-m\fP \fIJSON\fP, \fB\-\-meta=\fP\fIJSON\fP
Specify plaintext metadata for the Vault Item.  \fB\-mp\fP, \fB\-mpf\fP
\fIFILE\fP print the plaintext metadata as JSON.
.TP
\fB\-\-delete\fP
Delete the Vault Item.
.TP
\fB\-U\fP, \fB\-\-force\fP
Force the update of the Vault Item; undelete a deleted Vault Item.
.TP
\fB\-X\fP, \fB\-\-explore\fP
Print human\-readable information about the Vault Item.
.SS Stream Cipher Operations
All stream cipher actions require a
.B \-o
Vault Item that stores the symmetric cipher key, and may be combined with
the appropriate Vault Item options.
.TP
\fB\-c\fP \fIALGO\fP, \fB\-\-cipher=\fP\fIALGO\fP
Create a new stream cipher key for \fIALGO\fP (combine with \fB\-i\fP to
supply a raw key).  \fB\-cp\fP, \fB\-cpf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the algorithm
of the cipher key, if any; \fB\-cl\fP lists the supported algorithms.
.TP
\fB\-z\fP \fIJSON\fP, \fB\-\-cipher\-meta=\fP\fIJSON\fP
Specify secret metadata for the cipher key.  \fB\-zp\fP, \fB\-zpf\fP
\fIFILE\fP print the secret metadata as JSON.
.TP
\fB\-e\fP, \fB\-\-encrypt\fP
Stream encryption: \fB\-P\fP \(rt\(rt \fB\-C\fP, or stdin \(rt\(rt stdout.
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-decrypt\fP
Stream decryption: \fB\-C\fP \(rt\(rt \fB\-P\fP, or stdin \(rt\(rt stdout.
.TP
\fB\-P\fP[\fBf\fP] \fIFILE\fP, \fB\-\-plaintext=\fP\fIFILE\fP
Plaintext file for \fB\-e\fP | \fB\-d\fP.
.TP
\fB\-C\fP[\fBf\fP] \fIFILE\fP, \fB\-\-ciphertext=\fP\fIFILE\fP
Ciphertext file for \fB\-e\fP | \fB\-d\fP.
.SS Vault Key Operations
.TP
\fB\-k\fP \fIURI\fP, \fB\-\-vault\-key=\fP\fIURI\fP
Select a Vault Key.
.br
\fIURI\fP = "[ves:][//domain/]externalId/[userRef]"
.TP
\fB\-l\fP, \fB\-\-list\fP
List the Vault Items shared with the Vault Key (may be used without
.B \-k
to act on \fB\-a\fP | \fB\-A\fP).
.TP
\fB\-v\fP \fIVESKEY\fP, \fB\-\-veskey=\fP\fIVESKEY\fP
Supply a VESkey for a generated Vault Key, or for \fB\-k\fP.  \fB\-vp\fP,
\fB\-vpf\fP \fIFILE\fP print the current VESkey for \fB\-k\fP.
.TP
\fB\-g\fP, \fB\-\-generate\fP
Generate or re\-generate the Vault Key.
.TP
\fB\-y\fP \fIKEY\fP, \fB\-\-private\-key=\fP\fIKEY\fP
Supply a PEM private key to create the Vault Key.  \fB\-yf\fP \fIFILE\fP
reads the private key from the PEM \fIFILE\fP; \fB\-yp\fP, \fB\-ypf\fP
\fIFILE\fP print the PEM private key \(em non\-encrypted if the key is
unlocked, encrypted otherwise.
.TP
\fB\-Y\fP[\fBp\fP], \fB\-\-public\-key\fP, \fB\-Ypf\fP \fIFILE\fP
Print a PEM public key.
.TP
\fB\-G\fP \fIALGO\fP, \fB\-\-key\-algo=\fP\fIALGO\fP
Algorithm to generate the Vault Key.  \fB\-Gp\fP, \fB\-Gpf\fP \fIFILE\fP
print the algorithm name; \fB\-Gl\fP lists the supported algorithms.
.TP
\fB\-\-delete\fP
Delete the Vault Key (API restrictions apply).
.TP
\fB\-R\fP, \fB\-\-rekey\fP
Share all Vault Items on the key with the active key for the matching
Vault.
.TP
\fB\-K\fP, \fB\-\-propagate\fP
Share the VESkey vault item with the owner's respective Primary and/or App
Vault.
.TP
\fB\-\-manual\fP
Disable automatic propagation and rekeying for Temporary Vault Keys.
.TP
\fB\-X\fP, \fB\-\-explore\fP
Print human\-readable information about the Vault Key.
.SS Event Tracking
.TP
\fB\-W\fP [\fISPEC\fP], \fB\-\-events\fP[=\fISPEC\fP]
Track events.  The scope follows the selected object:
.B \-o
item,
.B \-k
key,
.B \-A
user, or
.B \-a
App Vault (use \fB//\fP\fIdomain\fP\fB//\fP for domain\-wide events).
.IP
\fISPEC\fP = [\fICOUNT\fP | =\fIID\fP[:\fICOUNT\fP]][+[\fISECONDS\fP]]
.RS
.TP 12
(none)
the last 16 events
.TP
\fICOUNT\fP
the last \fICOUNT\fP events
.TP
=\fIID\fP
events from event id \fIID\fP (up to 16)
.TP
=\fIID\fP:\fICOUNT\fP
\fICOUNT\fP events from event id \fIID\fP
.TP
+
follow: keep streaming new events
.TP
+\fISECONDS\fP
follow, but stop after \fISECONDS\fP
.TP
\fICOUNT\fP+
the last \fICOUNT\fP events, then follow
.RE
.IP
The default output is one tab\-separated line per event:
.IP
id <TAB> time <TAB> type <TAB> key_id <TAB> item_id <TAB> actor <TAB>
vault_uri <TAB> item_uri <TAB> ref_id <LF>
.IP
\fItime\fP is an ISO\-8601 UTC timestamp with milliseconds; \fIref_id\fP is
the session id, when available.  Combine with
.B \-X
for verbose, human\-readable output.
.SS Action Modifiers
.TP
\fB\-p\fP, \fB\-\-print\fP
Print the current value of the preceding option.
.TP
\fB\-f\fP \fIFILE\fP, \fB\-\-file=\fP\fIFILE\fP
Read a value from, or write a value to, a file.
.TP
\fB\-F\fP \fIFDESC\fP, \fB\-\-fd=\fP\fIFDESC\fP
Read a value from, or write a value to, a file descriptor (may be used
anywhere instead of \fB\-f\fP).
.SS Miscellaneous
.TP
\fB\-x\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display debugging messages.  \fB\-xx\fP enables more detailed debugging.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Suppress error messages except for argument errors; return error codes
only.  May be used with
.B \-o
without authentication to check whether a Vault Item exists, by exit code.
.TP
\fB\-V\fP, \fB\-\-version\fP
Print version information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Print the help screen and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B ves
returns 0 on success and a non\-zero libVES error code on failure.  With
.BR \-q ,
no messages are printed and only the exit code is returned, which makes
.B "\-q \-o"
.I URI
usable as a Vault Item existence check.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B VES_KEYSTORE
Colon\-separated list of Encryption Key Store directories.  When set, it
overrides the default per\-user location.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate the default key store at \fI~/.ves/\fP when
.B VES_KEYSTORE
is not set.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.ves/
Per\-user Encryption Key Store (used by
.BR \-E ).
.TP
.I /usr/share/ves/
System\-wide Key Store, searched after the per\-user store.
.SH EXAMPLES
Store text in a Vault Item and read it back:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ves \-a //demo/me@example.com/ \-E \-o note\-1 \-i "hello"
ves \-a //demo/me@example.com/ \-E \-o note\-1 \-ip
.EE
.RE
.PP
Share a Vault Item with another user:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ves \-a //demo/me@example.com/ \-E \-o note\-1 \e
    \-s //demo/friend@example.com/
.EE
.RE
.PP
Stream\-encrypt and decrypt a file with a cipher key stored in a Vault Item
(list algorithms with \fBves \-cl\fP):
.PP
.RS
.EX
ves \-a //demo/me@example.com/ \-E \-o backup \-c AES256GCM1K \e
    \-e \-Pf data.tar \-Cf data.tar.ves
ves \-a //demo/me@example.com/ \-E \-o backup \e
    \-d \-Cf data.tar.ves \-Pf data.tar
.EE
.RE
.PP
Follow account events, showing the last 20 then streaming new ones:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ves \-A me@example.com \-E \-W 20+
.EE
.RE
.PP
Check whether a Vault Item exists, by exit code only:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ves \-q \-o //demo/note\-1
.EE
.RE
